Exploration Update Summary:

Fosterville (Victoria):
- Gold-arsenic-antimony anomalism detected (peak 0.78 g/t Au) in aircore drilling.
- Anomaly open along strike; only one historic hole exists 1.6km north.
- Follow-up RC/aircore drilling planned to test IP chargeability anomaly source.

Glenlogan (NSW):
- Diamond drill hole SGLD0002 reached 798.3m, intersecting porphyry intrusives with alteration but no significant sulphides.
- Assays pending; further evaluation required.

Warraweena (NSW):
- Land access secured; drill permitting underway for target testing.

Materiality: Exploration results at Fosterville (near Agnico Eagle’s active mining) may indicate extension of mineralised structures. Glenlogan results inconclusive pending assays.

No capital/financial data disclosed.

Quarterly Report (June 2025) – Key Points

Operational Highlights:
- Southern Cross East Project:
- Completed 17-hole AC drilling program (1,125m) targeting 10km x 3.5km gold-in-soil anomaly.
- Anomalous intersections: 6m @ 0.19 g/t and 1m @ 0.14 g/t gold.
- Expanded tenure by 154 km²; high-resolution aeromagnetic survey planned.

  • Yule Project:
  • New tenement application adds 122 km², bringing total area to 678 km².
  • Planned 4,000m AC drill program targeting structural gold anomalies near Hemi deposit analogue.

Financial Highlights (Appendix 5B):
- Cash balance (30 June 2025): $720k (down from $1.04m last quarter).
- Quarterly cash burn: $319k (operating activities).
- Remaining funding runway: 2.3 quarters at current spend.
- Exploration expenditure: $248k for the quarter.

Additional Material Info:
- Tenement applications pending; exploration programs under review for Western Australia assets.

Quarterly Activities Report (June 2025) Highlights

  • Exploration Updates:
  • Lachlan Projects (NSW):
    • New gold targets identified; RC drilling at Sheepyard target (Walkers Hill trend) to commence late July.
    • 1,600-hole auger geochemical survey planned for July.
  • Macquarie Arc Projects (NSW):
    • IP/MT survey completed at Yarindury (porphyry copper-gold targets); drilling planned for September quarter.
    • 150-hole auger survey initiated at East Peak Hill (gold anomalies).

  • Gawler Projects (SA):

    • Diamond drilling at Mabel Creek intercepted Mo-REE alteration; further analysis ongoing for IOCG targets.

  • Financials:

  • Cash balance: $4.49 million (as of 30 June 2025).
  • Royalty receipts: $1.58 million from Wonmunna Iron Ore Project (total royalties to date: $31.3 million).

  • Exploration expenditure: $1.98 million for the quarter.

  • Upcoming Catalysts:

  • Drilling results from Sheepyard (Lachlan) and Yarindury (Macquarie Arc) in Q3/Q4 2025.

Key Focus for Trading/Capital Markets:

  • No capital raising or material corporate actions announced.
  • Operational focus on high-impact drilling programs to define gold/copper targets.
  • Liquidity remains stable with $4.49M cash (~6 quarters of funding per Appendix 5B).

Conclusion: Exploration progress and royalty cash flow provide near-term catalysts, but no immediate capital structure changes.

• Volume Trends: Q4 FY25 volumes show continued decline across most product categories vs prior periods, with few exceptions (e.g., Iplex NZ plastic pipes +10.1% YoY).
  • Steel & Concrete Weakness: Significant YoY drops in reinforcing (-12.5%), Stramit (-11.9%), and concrete pipe volumes (-15.1%).
  • Residential Collapse: Residential unit settlements plummeted -72% QoQ and -51.4% YoY.
  • Management Outlook: No meaningful volume recovery expected before FY27, per CEO.

No capital markets action required (operational update only).
